(362,100,2,'Joke about why did Trump back down on bombing Iran.','Why did Trump back down on bombing Iran?  \nHe thought the bomb would ruin the golf course.','active','2026-04-08 08:11:01','2026-04-08 08:11:01'),
(363,135,2,'Husband and wife issues','My wife says I\'m a great listener... But I only hear her when she\'s right.','active','2026-04-08 08:40:14','2026-04-08 08:40:14'),
(364,135,2,'Husband and wife issues','My wife says I never help with dishes. But I do—when she\'s not watching, and I\'m not caught.','active','2026-04-08 08:41:13','2026-04-08 08:41:13'),
(365,135,44,'Husband and wife issues','\"You can communicate with a stranger at a party, but your spouse? That\'s a whole different language. And if they ask you how your day was, you\'ll be telling them about your third cup of coffee.\"','active','2026-04-08 08:42:28','2026-04-08 08:42:28'),
(366,138,1,'why is my wife always right','My wife’s always right—because I’m the one who’s always wrong.  \nShe’s right, I’m just the wrong part of the equation.','active','2026-04-08 10:03:18','2026-04-08 10:03:18'),
(367,137,1,'electric vehicles','I tried charging my electric car. It took longer than my dating app to find a match.','active','2026-04-08 10:17:16','2026-04-08 10:17:16'),
(368,137,1,'electric vehicles','Why did the electric car get a ticket? It ran out of charge and couldn\'t pay.','active','2026-04-08 10:17:52','2026-04-08 10:17:52'),
(369,137,1,'electric vehicles','I tried to charge my electric car at a gas station. Now it\'s just a battery-powered treadmill for my wallet.','active','2026-04-08 10:18:16','2026-04-08 10:18:16'),
(370,137,1,'the price of petrol','Petrol prices keep rising, but I still drive like it\'s 1999.  \nNow I\'m a ghost in a gas-guzzling car.','active','2026-04-08 10:19:26','2026-04-08 10:19:26'),
(371,137,1,'prices rising','I used to buy a gallon of milk for a dollar. Now it\'s $5—same as my therapist\'s fee.','active','2026-04-08 10:20:16','2026-04-08 10:20:16'),
(372,137,1,'cost of living','I tried to save money by buying a house. Now I can\'t afford a couch.','active','2026-04-08 10:21:34','2026-04-08 10:21:34'),
(373,137,1,'cost of buying a house','I thought buying a house was an investment, but now I\'m paying rent to the bank.  \nFor life.','active','2026-04-08 10:26:34','2026-04-08 10:26:34'),
(374,139,1,'the economy','Why did the economist bring a ladder to the bank? To reach the top of the market!','active','2026-04-08 12:25:06','2026-04-08 12:25:06'),
(377,109,1,'Use observational sarcastic humor about life insurance strong punchline at the end of each segment','I pay life insurance to make sure my family grieves when I’m gone.  \nThey’ve already started the eulogy.','active','2026-04-08 14:12:51','2026-04-08 14:12:51'),
(378,140,1,'Histoire sur les beilges','Pourquoi les beilges ont-ils un échafaudage ? Pour demander des dons plus hauts !','active','2026-04-08 17:10:27','2026-04-08 17:10:27'),
(380,32,1,'Rahul Gandhi','Why did Rahul Gandhi switch to vegetarianism? He realized his family\'s legacy was on the menu!','active','2026-04-08 17:16:33','2026-04-08 17:16:33'),
(381,32,2,'software','Why did the programmer quit his job?  \nBecause he didn\'t get arrays; his boss crashed his code.','active','2026-04-08 17:18:11','2026-04-08 17:18:11'),
(382,140,10,'Histoire drole sur les belges','Why did the Belgian bring a ladder to the fry shop?  \nBecause he heard the fries were on the second floor!','active','2026-04-08 17:25:49','2026-04-08 17:25:49'),
(383,140,50,'Histoire Drole sur les belges','Belgians are the punchline of every history lesson.','active','2026-04-08 17:30:44','2026-04-08 17:30:44');
