(143,'joke_u1_20260402142814','2026-04-02 14:28:20','2026-04-02 19:28:20',2,'{\"id\":\"gen-1775140094-Ml3KOPORDFXKAjMjXAms\",\"object\":\"chat.completion\",\"created\":1775140094,\"model\":\"google-gemma-3n-e2b-it-free\",\"system_fingerprint\":null,\"choices\":[{\"index\":0,\"logprobs\":null,\"finish_reason\":\"length\",\"native_finish_reason\":\"MAX_TOKENS\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"**(Mic feedback squeal, I wince)**\\n\\nAlright, alright, settle down folks! So, I\'ve been thinking about life lately, right? And it\'s just...weird. \\n\\nLike, we spend so much time chasing goals. We\'re constantly striving for the next thing: a better job, a bigger house, a more impressive Instagram feed. \\n\\nBut then you realize, you\\u2019ve spent the last five years meticulously planning your career, and all you\\u2019ve achieved is slightly more beige clothing. \\n\\n**(Pause for laughter)**\\n\\nSeriously! I\\u2019m pretty sure beige is now considered a lifestyle. And the existential dread is *real*. \\n\\nI\\u2019m just trying to figure out if life is a race to the finish line, or a scenic route... that mostly involves potholes and questionable gas station coffee. \\n\\n**(Shrug)**\\n\\nBut hey, at least the potholes give you a good story for the grandkids, right?  They\",\"refusal\":null,\"reasoning\":null}}],\"usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":11,\"completion_tokens\":210,\"total_tokens\":221,\"cost\":\"0.00000000\",\"is_byok\":false,\"prompt_tokens_details\":{\"cached_tokens\":0,\"cache_write_tokens\":0,\"audio_tokens\":0,\"video_tokens\":0},\"cost_details\":{\"upstream_inference_cost\":\"0.00000000\",\"upstream_inference_prompt_cost\":\"0.00000000\",\"upstream_inference_completions_cost\":\"0.00000000\"},\"completion_tokens_details\":{\"reasoning_tokens\":0,\"image_tokens\":0,\"audio_tokens\":0}},\"promptToken\":11,\"completionToken\":210,\"cost\":0.0}'),
